To create VLAN Networks below things needs to be considerd:
1. To configure VLAN networks, switch ports connecting with servers should be configured as trunk ports.
2. You can create a range of VLAN networks or single VLAN network in openstack on single interface of
   compute nodes and network nodes. In both cases interface connecting switch should be trunk interfaces.
3. If you are configuring a FLAT type of network then trunk ports are not required because 
   FLAT networks do not tag traffic However VLAN networks tag traffic so in case of anytype of VLAN Network in OpenStack
   it is required that switch ports are configured as trunk ports.

Example of Network Creation:

neutron net-create vlan-network --provider:physical_network vlannet --provider:network_type vlan --provider:segmentation_id 317
neutron subnet-create vlan-network 172.16.17.0/24 --name vlan-subnet --allocation-pool start=172.16.17.200,end=172.16.17.254

neutron net-create trunk-network-1 --provider:physical_network trunknet --provider:network_type vlan --provider:segmentation_id 358
neutron subnet-create trunk-network-1 10.0.40.0/24 --name trunk-sbunet-1

neutron net-create trunk-network-2 --provider:physical_network trunknet --provider:network_type vlan --provider:segmentation_id 365
neutron subnet-create trunk-network-2 10.0.41.0/24 --name trunk-sbunet-2

neutron net-create trunk-network-3 --provider:physical_network trunknet --provider:network_type vlan --provider:segmentation_id 370
neutron subnet-create trunk-network-3 10.0.42.0/24 --name trunk-sbunet-3

neutron net-create fip-network-1 --provider:physical_network trunknet --provider:network_type vlan --router:external=True
neutron subnet-create fip-network-1 10.0.43.0/24 --name fip-subnet-1

neutron net-create vxlan-pvt-net-1
neutron subnet-create vxlan-pvt-net-1 10.0.9.0/24 --name vxlan-pvt-subnet-1 --gateway 10.0.9.1

neutron router-create router
neutron router-gateway-set router fip-network-1 
neutron router-interface-add router vxlan-pvt-subnet-1

